rojects that design across cultural difference. The book's structure, method, and arguments are dialogically assembled around narratives told by Indigenous people of their pursuit of public recognition, spatial justice, and architectural presence in settler dominated societies. Possibilities for decolonising architecture emerge through these accounts"--cProvided by publisher.  a43 0aArts facilitiesxSocial aspects. 0aArchitecturexPhilosophy. 0aCultural landscapes. 0aIndigenous peoples. 0aArchitects and community.1 aPieris, Anoma,eauthor. 0aRoutledge research in architecture.423Cover imageuhttp://images.tandf.co.uk/common/jackets/websmall/978041581/9780415815321.jpg  aNA 6811 M38 2015hUAHS-Bi0162035241452  aNA 6811 M38 2015wLCc1i0162035241452d1/14/2017e1/14/2017kCHECKEDOUTlON_SHELFmUAHSSn4p$150.00rMsYtBOOKu2/19/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2004036004bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/71099498